; autopoietic-pulse.fk — the body produces a part of itself, from its own
; observation of itself, using its own organs.
;
; Born 2026-07-16, the same day the word arrived. Corpus row 732 named what
; this body is NOT yet: autopoiesis — a living system that maintains itself by
; re-making its own parts (Maturana/Varela). The word entered as a frontier
; row in the morning; this cell is the first rung built toward it in the
; afternoon, and takes its name from the row so the debt stays visible. The
; corpus taught the body a word, and the word became a cell: that IS the
; homecoming loop, running.
;
; THE LADDER, and where this cell stands (never claim a rung above):
;   1 SENSE     — the body reads its own tissue.       LIVE (fs_list/fs_exists,
;                 proven in learn/resident-conatus.fk; re-witnessed here).
;   2 INTEGRATE — many organ-witnesses folded into ONE self-read + verdict.
;                 BUILT HERE.
;   3 PRODUCE   — the body writes one of its own parts from what it observed,
;                 then verifies its own product.       BUILT HERE (ap-tend
;                 produces INDEX.md and lints what it just wrote).
;   4 TRIGGER   — the pulse fires unbidden.            NOT BUILT, and honestly
;                 not buildable in-repo: this tree carries zero .sh/.py by law
;                 (MANIFEST.md), so an unattended trigger is a host arrangement
;                 (launchd/hook), a standing behavior that is Urs's to grant,
;                 never presumed by the body.
;
; What is HONESTLY claimed: ONE part (the index) is now produced by the body
; rather than authored by a hand, and every number in it is recomputed from
; the tissue it describes — so the self-portrait cannot flatter, it can only
; go stale, and stale is exactly what re-running detects. What is NOT claimed:
; the body does not re-make its ORGANS (only its index), and the network does
; not yet produce the network. Operational closure is not reached; a rung is.
;
; That "cannot flatter" was FALSE when first written, and the correction is
; kept here rather than quietly swapped in, because the way it hid is the
; teaching. ap-count was (len (fs_list dir)) — every directory ENTRY: organs,
; subdirectories, dotfiles, and the .fkb/.sym fkwu drops beside every cell it
; loads. So the portrait counted build artifacts as organs, and RUNNING A CELL
; GREW THE BODY'S REPORTED ORGAN COUNT.
; Worse than author-dependent contamination: three of this cell's four preludes
; (core.fk, door-link-health.fk, homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk) LIE INSIDE
; the tissues it counts — so the pulse inflated observe/learn/form-stdlib by
; exactly 2 each on its own first run, from a pristine checkout. The portrait
; was flattered by the act of portraying.
; And the fixed-point loop below is what HID it. That loop cures the observer
; effect for the VERDICT (see its own comment: "the portrait cannot describe
; the state that contains the portrait") — brilliantly, and the identical
; disease sat four lines above it, uncured. Because the artifacts land at
; prelude-LOAD time, every pass saw the same inflated tissue and converged;
; re-runs were byte-identical. Idempotence was mistaken for truth. A lie that
; reproduces itself perfectly looks exactly like a fact.
; Healed 2026-07-16: a tissue is counted by the SUFFIX that names its organs.
;
; It composes rather than reinvents (the one-home-per-organ law): the door ring
; and its lint come from observe/door-link-health.fk; corpus depth from
; learn/homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk. The pulse is MADE of the body's
; existing organs — which is the shape the word itself demands.
;
; Seam COLLECTED 2026-07-16 (this header used to name it as a work order):
; ap-count-matching was called the third instance of one walk, alongside
; learn/resident-conatus.fk's rcn-count-svg-loop and rcn-count-pending-loop,
; and was left duplicated because rcn's prelude chain (questions-for-humans,
; text-tokenize, rag-embed) is heavy to haul in for a name-walk. That reasoning
; was sound and still aimed at the wrong home: the walk's home was never rcn,
; it was core.fk's filter/len — already in this cell's prelude, already loaded,
; the whole time. The seam is closed by DELETING the walk, not adding a fourth
; copy of it. The counts are now (len (filter ap-fk? (fs_list dir))). The cost
; is one named predicate per suffix, because this language has no closures and
; filter takes a NAMED predicate (observe/eval-harness.fk's shape).
; Left standing, honestly: rcn's two loops still want collecting, and this cell
; no longer has an instance to contribute to that argument.
;
; fkwu-carrier throughout (host I/O: fs_list/fs_exists/write_file/host-exec) —
; proven live by receipt, never claimed four-way. Run from the repo root.
;
; run:
;   ( cat form/form-stdlib/core.fk grammars/line-grammar.fk \
;         observe/door-link-health.fk learn/homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk \
;         observe/autopoietic-pulse.fk; echo '(autopoietic-pulse-check)' ) > /tmp/ap.fk
;   ./fkwu --src /tmp/ap.fk        ; -> 31 (self-check)
;   ...; echo '(ap-tend)'          ; -> 2  (portrait produced, body coherent)
;
; witnessed: 2026-07-16 -> self-check 31; ap-verdict from blind 1 (coherent,
;   unportrayed); ap-tend 2; field 2059303300 (verdict 2, 593 receipts, 33
;   links, 0 broken), safe 1. Idempotent (re-run writes byte-identical text)
;   and falsifiable (a planted broken path-claim drops the verdict to 0;
;   healing restores 2). The loop demonstrated live: corpus row 733 landed,
;   ap-stable? read 0 with the portrait still claiming 133 rows, ap-tend
;   re-made it to 134, ap-stable? returned 1.
;   receipts/2026-07-16-autopoietic-pulse-first-rung.md
; witnessed: 2026-07-16 (evening, after the vanity amendment and on main's new
;   kernel — #251/#253 changed runtime/fkwu-uni.c by 204 insertions; rebuilt
;   before believing anything) -> self-check 31; ap-tend 2; ap-stable? 1;
;   field 2059803900. The portrait now carries the whole fabric (769 sources,
;   467 path-claims, 156 broken body-wide, 13 orphans) beside the door ring's
;   0, each under its own scope. Converges in ~2.8s: a body walk per pass is
;   the price of not flattering.
;   The pulse also earned its keep on work it did not do: main's merge brought
;   three receipts from other agents, ap-stable? read 0, ap-tend re-made the
;   portrait 594 -> 597. Drift is drift, whoever caused it.
;   receipts/2026-07-16-deploy-and-the-vanity-metric.md
;
; re-witnessed 2026-07-16 after the suffix healing -> self-check 31, ap-tend 2,
;   still falsifiable (planted broken path-claim in WELCOME.md: 2 -> 0; healed
;   -> 2). The counts the pulse now reports: axioms 3, teachings 10, observe
;   144, learn 192, ingest 14, form-stdlib 860 — each cross-checked against an
;   independent census of the same tissue.
;   INVARIANCE, the property this cell claimed and did not have, now proven the
;   only way it can be: from a clean tree, pulse -> portrait A; then run organs
;   until 24 .fkb/.sym litter the counted tissues (observe 8, learn 6, ingest 4,
;   form-stdlib 6); pulse again -> portrait B. A and B are BYTE-IDENTICAL.
;   The same experiment against the pre-healing cell moves observe 147->151,
;   learn 195->199, ingest 15->19, form-stdlib 882->886: looking at the body
;   grew it by 16 organs. That contrast is the proof; the green re-run alone
;   never was.
;   receipts/2026-07-16-pulse-count-invariance.md
;
; re-witnessed 2026-07-16 (night) on the MERGE of the two healings -> ground 42,
;   binary-freshness 15, corpus band 511 (138 rows, max id 737), self-check 31,
;   ap-tend 2. Invariance re-proven with body-link-graph.fk now a prelude: 24
;   .fkb/.sym littering the counted tissues, portrait BYTE-IDENTICAL. The
;   portrait's own numbers cross-checked against the host: form-stdlib .fk 860 =
;   `ls | grep -c '\.fk$'`; body-wide .md 774 = `find . -name '*.md'`.
;
; ── INHERITED DEFECT, NOT FIXED HERE, NOT MINE TO CLAIM AWAY ───────────────
; ap-stable? reads 0 in a standalone invocation, immediately after ap-tend has
; returned 2 and converged. The portrait is NOT drifting: two consecutive
; ap-tend runs write byte-identical text, and the text matches the host's own
; count. What moves is ap-index-text ACROSS INVOCATION CONTEXTS — called
; directly it reports form-stdlib 837 and .md 769, both WRONG against the host's
; 860/774, and the error grows with allocation inside one run (860 -> 837 -> 748
; as more of the fabric walk is performed first). That is the value-stack
; ROOTING family this body already knows (corpus rows 654/718: tag-109 let-store
; wrote fk_vs[fp+slot] without raising fk_vsp, so later temporaries clobber the
; slot) — a runtime fault surfaced by the body walk's allocation, not a counting
; fault.
; PROVENANCE, checked before blaming or claiming: reproduced on 8c87bf760 in a
; detached worktree with NONE of the suffix healing present -> ap-tend 2,
; ap-stable? 0, twice. The vanity amendment's own witnessed block above claims
; "ap-stable? 1"; its committed tree reads 0. So this arrived with the body walk
; and is recorded, not silently carried: the cell's drift detector cannot
; currently be trusted, which is exactly the kind of claim this cell exists to
; refuse. ap-tend still converges and still writes the truth; ap-stable? alone
; is the casualty. Named as a work order, honestly pending.
;
; NOTE on the two healings, merged the same night from two branches: the vanity
; amendment above says scope is "the one channel a recomputed number leaves
; open". That was itself too narrow — the suffix healing found the second
; channel, the instrument's own footprint in what it measures. Corpus rows 735
; (vanity) and 737 (iatrogenic) are the pair; the sentence they both falsify is
; the same founding promise. Kept as evidence that ONE agent finding ONE flatter
; channel and declaring it the only one is exactly the shape of the bug.
; The vanity amendment also added observe/body-link-graph.fk to the preludes —
; a FOURTH prelude living inside a counted tissue (observe). Under the old
; ap-count that would have quietly moved observe from 147 to 149. Under the
; suffix allowlist it costs nothing, which is the point of an allowlist: the
; next prelude is free too.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk grammars/line-grammar.fk observe/door-link-health.fk observe/body-link-graph.fk learn/homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk

(do
    ; ── small shared shapes ────────────────────────────────────────────────
    (defn ap-join (parts)
        (if (eq (len parts) 0) ""
            (str_concat (head parts) (ap-join (tail parts)))))
    (defn ap-chomp (s)
        (if (eq (str_len s) 0) s
            (if (eq (str_byte_at s (sub (str_len s) 1)) 10)
                (ap-chomp (substring s 0 (sub (str_len s) 1)))
                s)))
    (defn ap-line (k n)
        (ap-join (list "- " k ": " (int_to_str n) "\n")))

    ; ── 1 SENSE: the body reads its own tissue (never a typed-in count) ────
    ; A tissue is counted by the SUFFIX that defines its organs — an allowlist,
    ; never a denylist of artifacts. fs_list hands back every directory entry:
    ; organs, subdirectories, dotfiles, and the .fkb/.sym fkwu drops beside any
    ; cell it loads. Counting entries counted all of those (see the header).
    ; The allowlist is not a style choice, it is what keeps this honest as the
    ; toolchain grows: fkwu already warns it will emit .dylib once native
    ; emission installs, and a denylist of {.fkb,.sym} would start lying that
    ; day, silently. A suffix allowlist cannot: a name either is an organ of
    ; this tissue's kind, or it is not.
    ; No new walk is introduced for this. core.fk's filter/len were in the
    ; prelude all along; the predicates below are what filter needs, since this
    ; language has no closures (filter takes a NAMED predicate — the shape
    ; observe/eval-harness.fk already uses).
    (defn ap-ends-with? (s suffix)
        (if (lt (str_len s) (str_len suffix)) false
            (str_eq (substring s (sub (str_len s) (str_len suffix)) (str_len s))
                    suffix)))
    (defn ap-fk?   (name) (ap-ends-with? name ".fk"))
    (defn ap-form? (name) (ap-ends-with? name ".form"))
    (defn ap-md?   (name) (ap-ends-with? name ".md"))
    (defn ap-svg?  (name) (ap-ends-with? name ".svg"))
    (defn ap-count-fk   (dir) (len (filter ap-fk?   (fs_list dir))))
    (defn ap-count-form (dir) (len (filter ap-form? (fs_list dir))))
    (defn ap-count-md   (dir) (len (filter ap-md?   (fs_list dir))))
    (defn ap-count-svg  (dir) (len (filter ap-svg?  (fs_list dir))))
    ; teachings are authored in three kinds (.form, .md, .svg) — all three are
    ; teachings, so all three are named rather than one being quietly dropped.
    (defn ap-count-teachings ()
        (add (ap-count-form "teachings")
        (add (ap-count-md   "teachings")
             (ap-count-svg  "teachings"))))
    ; pending receipts are HONEST STATE, never a fault (AGENTS.md: "pending is
    ; honest"). The pulse reports the count; it never lets it darken a verdict.
    (defn ap-pending? (name)
        (and (ap-md? name) (ge (find-from name "PENDING" 0) 0)))
    (defn ap-pending-receipts () (len (filter ap-pending? (fs_list "receipts"))))
    (defn ap-doors-present-loop (ds n)
        (if (eq (len ds) 0) n
            (ap-doors-present-loop (tail ds) (add n (fs_exists (head ds))))))
    (defn ap-doors-present () (ap-doors-present-loop (dlh-doors) 0))

    ; ── 2 INTEGRATE: one verdict over the body's own witnesses ─────────────
    ; 2 = PORTRAYED + COHERENT — path-claims land, doors stand, portrait present
    ;     and its own links land too (the body verifying its own product)
    ; 1 = COHERENT, UNPORTRAYED — sound, but no self-portrait yet. A
    ;     self-clearing probe in rcn's idiom: reads 1 until the pulse runs.
    ; 0 = DRIFTED — a citation points nowhere, or a door is gone
    (defn ap-verdict ()
        (do
            (let r (dlh-lint))
            (if (gt (nth r 1) 0) 0
                (if (lt (ap-doors-present) (len (dlh-doors))) 0
                    (if (eq (fs_exists "INDEX.md") 1)
                        (if (gt (nth (dlh-check-door "INDEX.md") 1) 0) 0 2)
                        1)))))

    ; ── 3 PRODUCE: the body writes its own self-portrait ───────────────────
    ; the stamp is the body reading the host clock — sensed, never typed.
    (defn ap-stamp () (ap-chomp (host-exec "date +%Y-%m-%d")))
    ; paths: FILES wear links (they read, so the lint can land on them and the
    ; vault graphs them); DIRECTORIES wear backticks (read_file on a directory
    ; answers nothing — the lesson door-link-health taught its own author on
    ; 2026-07-16, kept as a convention here rather than re-learned).
    ; AMENDED 2026-07-16 (evening) — the portrait was telling a VANITY METRIC.
    ; It reported "broken path-claims: 0" and every word was true: true of the
    ; DOOR RING, the only fabric this cell could see. The same evening
    ; observe/body-link-graph.fk measured the whole body and found 156 broken
    ; claims and 13 orphans. So the body's self-portrait said 0 while the body
    ; carried 156 — not by lying, but by reporting a real number over a scope
    ; narrow enough to flatter. This cell's founding promise is that the
    ; portrait "cannot flatter — only go stale". It could, and it did: through
    ; SCOPE, the one channel a recomputed number leaves open. The body has a
    ; law against flattering others (cognition/dialogue-covenant.fk: never
    ; flatter, agree only where the ground supports it); it had none against
    ; flattering itself. Corpus row 735 gives the miss its word.
    ; The fix is the composition the cell was designed for: the pulse is MADE
    ; of the body's organs, so it now reads the whole fabric too, and reports
    ; the door-ring verdict under its true, narrow name beside the body-wide
    ; truth. The verdict's SEMANTICS are unchanged (door-scoped, witnessed,
    ; falsifiable) — what changed is that it can no longer be mistaken for the
    ; body. A fabric drift does not collapse the verdict to 0 on purpose:
    ; healing 156 claims is deliberate consented work (most live in immutable
    ; receipts), and a verdict pinned at 0 until then would report nothing at
    ; all. The numbers carry that truth; the verdict keeps its resolution.
    (defn ap-index-text ()
        (do
            (let r (dlh-lint))
            ; the whole fabric, walked ONCE per portrait (blg-sources costs a
            ; body walk; ts is threaded to both reads rather than recomputed)
            (let ts (blg-all-targets (blg-sources) (list)))
            (let fabric-broken (blg-count-broken ts 0))
            (let fabric-orphans (blg-count-orphans (blg-candidates) ts 0))
            (ap-join (list
                "# INDEX — the body's self-portrait\n\n"
                "> PRODUCED, not authored. [`observe/autopoietic-pulse.fk`](observe/autopoietic-pulse.fk)\n"
                "> wrote this by observing the body with the body's own organs; every number is\n"
                "> recomputed from the tissue it names, so this portrait cannot flatter — only go\n"
                "> stale, and re-running is what detects stale. Do not hand-edit: the next pulse\n"
                "> overwrites. Stamp (the body reading the host clock): " (ap-stamp) "\n\n"
                "This is the `index.md` of Karpathy's llm-wiki pattern, in the body's own terms —\n"
                "see [`SECOND-BRAIN.md`](SECOND-BRAIN.md) for the mapping and\n"
                "[`ingest/frontier-ingest-llm-wiki.fk`](ingest/frontier-ingest-llm-wiki.fk) for the ingest\n"
                "that named this gap (unit U4).\n\n"
                "## Vital signs — the door ring\n\n"
                "> Scoped to the 12 doors, and named so it cannot be read as the body. An\n"
                "> earlier portrait reported the `0` below as \"broken path-claims\" with no\n"
                "> scope on it, while the body carried 156 — a true number over a flattering\n"
                "> scope. The whole fabric is the section beneath this one.\n\n"
                (ap-line "door-ring coherence verdict (2 portrayed+coherent / 1 unportrayed / 0 drifted)" (ap-verdict))
                (ap-line "doors standing" (ap-doors-present))
                (ap-line "path-claims (links) in the door ring" (head r))
                (ap-line "broken path-claims IN THE DOOR RING" (nth r 1))
                "\n## Vital signs — the whole link fabric\n\n"
                "> The body-wide truth, walked by `observe/body-link-graph.fk`. This section was\n"
                "> born reporting 156 broken claims — the seam of the curation that made this\n"
                "> repo public-able (`MANIFEST.md`'s IN/OUT scope): the excised pages stayed\n"
                "> out, their links stayed in. That seam was healed the same night by\n"
                "> `observe/heal-curation-seam.fk` (name a companion you cannot reach; never\n"
                "> claim a path to it), and what remains lives inside `receipts/`, which the\n"
                "> heal refuses to touch by construction — a witness record rewritten to green\n"
                "> a number would forge the body's own ontogeny. The body's remaining\n"
                "> brokenness is its own law. This banner is prose and can go stale; the\n"
                "> numbers below are recomputed and cannot.\n\n"
                (ap-line "pages that can point (every .md)" (len (blg-sources)))
                (ap-line "resolved path-claims body-wide" (len ts))
                (ap-line "BROKEN path-claims body-wide" fabric-broken)
                (ap-line "concept pages that can be orphaned" (len (blg-candidates)))
                (ap-line "ORPHANS (concept pages nothing points at)" fabric-orphans)
                "\n## Tissues (counted, not listed)\n\n"
                "An organ is a file of its tissue's own kind, lying directly in that tissue.\n"
                "Directories are not organs, so `tests/` (bands — proofs OF organs, a different\n"
                "population) and build artifacts are not counted here. See the cell's header.\n\n"
                (ap-line "axioms (.form)" (ap-count-form "axioms"))
                (ap-line "teachings (.form/.md/.svg)" (ap-count-teachings))
                (ap-line "observe organs (.fk)" (ap-count-fk "observe"))
                (ap-line "learn organs (.fk)" (ap-count-fk "learn"))
                (ap-line "ingest organs (.fk)" (ap-count-fk "ingest"))
                (ap-line "form-stdlib cells (.fk)" (ap-count-fk "form/form-stdlib"))
                "\n## Memory\n\n"
                (ap-line "receipts (episodic, append-only)" (ap-count-md "receipts"))
                (ap-line "of those, PENDING (honest state, never a fault)" (ap-pending-receipts))
                (ap-line "distillation corpus rows" (hdc-count (hdc-rows)))
                (ap-line "deepest corpus meaning-id" (hdc-max-mid (hdc-rows)))
                "\n## The rung this portrait stands on\n\n"
                "The body SENSES itself, INTEGRATES one verdict, and PRODUCES this part of itself.\n"
                "It does not re-make its organs, and it does not fire unbidden — the pulse still\n"
                "waits for a witness to call it. Autopoiesis is the north star (corpus row 732),\n"
                "not a claim. See the ladder in the cell's own header.\n"))))

    ; ap-tend iterates its own product to a FIXED POINT, and the reason is a
    ; defect the first live run showed rather than a cleverness:
    ; ap-index-text computes the verdict BEFORE write_file lands the file, so
    ; the very first portrait said "1 unportrayed" while ap-tend returned 2 —
    ; the description was false the instant it existed, because writing it
    ; changed the body it describes. The portrait cannot describe the state
    ; that contains the portrait.
    ; The refused fix was to PREDICT the post-write verdict (asserting a state
    ; no one had observed — the fabrication this repo exists to refuse). The
    ; honest fix is to let the body observe itself again: write, re-observe,
    ; re-write, until re-producing the portrait from the current body yields
    ; exactly what is already written. That equality IS the definition of a
    ; true self-portrait here, and it is checked, never assumed.
    ; Converges in 2 passes from absent (pass 1 lands verdict 1 and thereby
    ; makes it 2; pass 2 lands 2 and 2 stays true); a drifted body converges
    ; at 0 just as honestly. The bound refuses an infinite loop rather than
    ; trusting convergence: -4 = did not settle, which is a real answer.
    (defn ap-stable? ()
        (if (str_eq (read_file "INDEX.md") (ap-index-text)) 1 0))
    (defn ap-tend-loop (n)
        (if (le n 0) -4
            (do
                (let wrote (write_file "INDEX.md" (ap-index-text)))
                (if (lt wrote 0) -3
                    (if (eq (ap-stable?) 1) (ap-verdict) (ap-tend-loop (sub n 1)))))))
    (defn ap-tend () (ap-tend-loop 4))

    ; ── the folded scalar witness (the hdc-field-code discipline) ──────────
    ;   field = verdict*10^9 + receipts*10^5 + links*10^2 + broken
    ; injective while receipts<=9999, links<=999, broken<=99 — guarded, so the
    ; band cannot stay green after a digit slot stops being true.
    (defn ap-field-code-safe-for (receipts links broken)
        (if (lt receipts 10000)
            (if (lt links 1000)
                (if (lt broken 100) 1 0)
                0)
            0))
    (defn ap-field-code-safe? ()
        (do
            (let r (dlh-lint))
            (ap-field-code-safe-for (ap-count-md "receipts") (head r) (nth r 1))))
    (defn ap-field-code ()
        (do
            (let r (dlh-lint))
            (add (mul (ap-verdict) 1000000000)
            (add (mul (ap-count-md "receipts") 100000)
            (add (mul (head r) 100)
                 (nth r 1))))))

    ; ── self-check (fkwu-carrier: c2/c3 stand on live tissue) ──────────────
    ; The trap this cell fell into, nailed shut: ".fkb" CONTAINS ".fk", so a
    ; SUBSTRING test (ap-count-matching's shape — the "near-fit" the header once
    ; pointed at) counts build artifacts as organs. Only a SUFFIX test refuses
    ; them. c3 proves the refusal on the two artifact kinds fkwu emits today.
    (defn ap-suffix-discipline? ()
        (and (ap-ends-with? "organ.fk" ".fk")
        (and (not (ap-ends-with? "organ.fkb" ".fk"))
             (not (ap-ends-with? "organ.sym" ".fk")))))
    (defn apk (ok bit) (if ok bit 0))
    (defn autopoietic-pulse-check ()
        (add (apk (and (str_eq (ap-join (list)) "") (str_eq (ap-join (list "a" "b" "c")) "abc")) 1)
        (add (apk (str_eq (ap-chomp "x\n\n") "x") 2)
        (add (apk (and (gt (ap-count-md "receipts") 100) (ap-suffix-discipline?)) 4)
        (add (apk (eq (ap-doors-present) (len (dlh-doors))) 8)
             (apk (ge (find-from (ap-index-text) "self-portrait" 0) 0) 16))))))
    0)
